claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: Two Kaplan–Meier plots showing cumulative incidence of culture-positive CDC-defined influenza-like illness for influenza A (top) and influenza B (bottom) during the surveillance period in placebo (solid line) and FluBlok (dotted line) recipients, with associated vaccine efficacy data in text below. The figure presents incidence curves and efficacy percentages; it does not provide any information on antigenic matching to WHO- or FDA-selected strains and therefore does not support the claim.
